## Environment Configuration

### ✅ GOOD - Secure Environment Variables

```typescript
// sidepanel/src/config.ts
const API_URL = import.meta.env.VITE_API_URL || 'http://localhost:3000'
const CLERK_PUB_KEY = import.meta.env.VITE_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY

if (!CLERK_PUB_KEY) {
  throw new Error('Missing VITE_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY')
}

export const config = {
  apiUrl: API_URL,
  clerkPublicKey: CLERK_PUB_KEY,
}

// .env.local (never commit!)
VITE_API_URL=https://api.prophet.com
VITE_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_live_...
```

### ❌ BAD - Exposed Secrets

```typescript
// ❌ Never expose secret keys
const ANTHROPIC_API_KEY = 'sk_live_...' // EXPOSED TO USERS!

// ❌ Never use NEXT_PUBLIC_ prefix for extension secrets
// Process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_ANTHROPIC_KEY // This gets bundled!
```

