## Side Panel Messaging

### ✅ GOOD - Proper Extension Messaging

```typescript
// If you need to communicate between extension parts (content script, background, sidepanel)
// Use chrome.runtime.sendMessage for small, one-off messages

// sidepanel/App.tsx - Request data from content script
async function getPageContext() {
  try {
    const response = await chrome.tabs.query({ active: true, currentWindow: true })
    const tab = response[0]

    const message = await chrome.tabs.sendMessage(tab.id!, {
      action: 'GET_PAGE_CONTEXT',
    })

    return message.context
  } catch (error) {
    console.warn('Content script not available:', error)
    return null
  }
}

// content-script.ts - Respond to sidepanel request
chrome.runtime.onMessage.addListener((request, sender, sendResponse) => {
  if (request.action === 'GET_PAGE_CONTEXT') {
    sendResponse({
      context: {
        pageTitle: document.title,
        pageUrl: window.location.href,
        selectedText: window.getSelection()?.toString() || '',
      },
    })
  }
})
```

### ❌ BAD - Insecure Messaging

```typescript
// ❌ Don't send sensitive data through messaging (can be intercepted)
chrome.runtime.sendMessage({ apiKey: 'sk_live_...' })

// ❌ Don't trust user-provided data from page context
const userInput = await getPageContext() // Content scripts can be manipulated
// Always validate on backend
```

